{:name "Fee drives breach; improving inbound permitted"
 :tags #{:policies :curative}

 ;; Customer is opened, funded to +100, then a 250 fee drives them
 ;; to -150. The available-balance rule's `:improving` allowance
 ;; permits an inbound that strictly reduces the breach (-150 →
 ;; -50). This is the load-bearing scenario: if the policy
 ;; evaluator rejects the second inbound, the customer can never
 ;; recover from a fee-driven breach.
 :given
 [{:command :open-account     :args []}
  {:command :inbound-transfer :args [:acct-0 100]}
  {:command :apply-fee        :args [:acct-0 250]}]

 :when
 [{:command :inbound-transfer :args [:acct-0 100]}]

 :then
 [{:command :assert-outcome :args [:succeeded]}
  {:command :assert-balance :args [:acct-0 -50]}]}
